<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yee explains that part of the hook of the game is that a player can succeed quickly when they start playing, but the longer they play, the longer it takes for the awards to be received. For example, a beginning player can gain a level in five to 10 minutes but a more experienced player can take anywhere from five to 20 hours to gain a level.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Last time I checked, all games become more difficult as you advance.  Hell, even Scrabble gets to be a pain in the ass (damn all of you with your stupid 3 letter words in the corners).<br>
<br>
Overall, I see someone who made a last ditch effort to try to gather some information that would appear acceptable to people who largely have no clue what EverQuest is.<br>
<br>
<br>
[side note:  I'm not saying I don't think this game is addictive, just that this article is a pretty poor attempt at proving it]<br>
