That's exactly what can be done with statistics. The difference between a sample of 3,000 people and a total research of 400,000 people, is that the result from the sample will have an uncertainty which can be measured with some degree of confidence, while a total research would give us 'exact' answers. What makes you think the sample population doesn't share the characteristics of the total EQ community?<br>
<br>
There are many misconceptions about statistics and it's very easy to make blunders when making a study like the one we are talking about, even when asking a simple question like 'Are you addicted to EQ? Answer Yes or No'. There are only two answers to this question, however the opinions about the meaning of 'addicted' will vary among people. Im quite sure there are some softcore players out there, that play like 1 hour every other day and consider themself addicts, while some of the hardcore players might be playing 10 hours a day without admitting they are addicted. If you think of it, addicted people have a tendency to not admit they have an addiction. So even if we were to make a total research, we would have some degree of error. <br>
<br>
However that's not the case here. Nick Yee formulated his question in a different way to avoid misconceptions. He asked those 3,166 people if they admit being addicted to the game and 50% of them admitted they were. The conclusion is: 50% of all Everquest players would admit being addicted to the game, if asked.<br>
<br>
The journalism might or might not be low-quality. I don't know since I'm a europud, but that doesn't mean the research was low-quality. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandarie>Nandarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 3119<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(6/21/03 12:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3321.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mwscomp.com/movies/grail/jpgs/timencha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stupid article EQ Bashing</span><hr size=1> Facts can prove anything, though.  That's why, to determine whether it is a worthwhile read, we have to look at the quality of journalism, which is piss poor. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/NandSig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
